toward, or connected with commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

Commercial use is not allowed under this license. Commercial use includes,
without limitation:

- monetized streams;
- ad-supported streams;
- paid services;
- managed hosting, software-as-a-service, or platform-as-a-service offerings;
- agency use;
- consulting-for-pay use;
- selling support, setup, integration, operation, or customization services;
- using Stream247 for a customer, client, employer, or commercial project;
- internal business use that supports commercial operations.

To use Stream247 commercially, you must obtain a separate written commercial
license from the project owner before that use begins.

3. Redistribution And Modified Forks

You may redistribute Stream247 or a modified fork only under this license or
under a separate written license from the project owner. You must include this
license, preserve copyright notices, and clearly mark material changes you
made.

4. Public Stream Attribution

Every public stream produced, automated, scheduled, controlled, or otherwise
operated with Stream247 must include a visible repository link:

https://github.com/DrJakeberg/stream247

The minimum acceptable location is the stream description, channel panel, or
an equivalent always-visible public page associated with the stream. The link
must be reasonably easy for viewers to find. This requirement applies to
public streams even when the stream is non-commercial.

5. No Runtime Enforcement

This license is enforced by its legal terms. Stream247 does not need to add
runtime license checks or phone-home behavior to enforce this license.

